                  <decoDesc>
                  <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d1"><locus target="#iv(erso)" facs="002">Fol. iv(erso)</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1035HolyMan">Holy Man Portrait</ref> <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4306GabraMa">Gabra Manfas Qǝddus</persName> /&gt;</desc></decoNote>
                  <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d2"><locus target="#iiv(erso)" facs="003">Fol. iiv(erso)</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1035HolyMan">Holy Man Portrait</ref> <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS9162TaklaHa">Takla Hāymānot</persName> </desc></decoNote>
                  <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d3"><locus target="#iiir(ecto)" facs="003">Fol. iiir(ecto)</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1035HolyMan">Holy Man Portrait</ref>, with crow (faded) </desc></decoNote>
                  <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d4"><locus target="#iiiv(erso)" facs="004">Fol. iiiv(erso)</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1086StrikingHead">The Striking of the Head, ኵርዓተ፡ ርእሱ፡</ref></desc></decoNote>
                  <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d5"><locus target="#ivr(ecto)" facs="004">Fol. ivr(ecto)</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1049Resurrection">Resurrection of Jesus</ref></desc></decoNote>
                  <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d6"><locus target="#67r" facs="071">Fol. 67r</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1005Crucifixion">Crucifixion of Jesus</ref></desc></decoNote>
                  <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d7"><locus target="#68v" facs="073">Fol. 68v</locus></decoNote>
                  <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d8"><locus target="#69r" facs="073">Fol. 69r</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1031VirginAndChild">, with patron prostrate before them</ref> with caption “How Mämre Gäbäyähu pleaded.”</desc></decoNote>
                  <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d9"><locus target="#69v" facs="074">Fol. 69v</locus><desc>Crude drawing of a <term key="cross" ana="#cross"/> with caption “This is the cross and any one who erases it is …”</desc></decoNote>
                  <decoNote xml:id="d10">
                    Several of the illuminations in this book are protected by pieces of fabric:
                    1) there is one piece of fabric which separates the illuminations on <locus target="#iiv(erso) #3r" facs="003 007">folss. iiv(erso), 3r, </locus>;
                    2) one covering the illumination on <locus target="#iiiv(erso)" facs="004">iiiv(erso), </locus>;
                    3) one covering the illumination on <locus target="#ivr(ecto)" facs="004">ivr(ecto), </locus>;
                    4) one covering the illumination on <locus target="#67r" facs="071">67r, </locus>; and
                    5) one that separates the illuminations on folios <locus target="#68v #69r" facs="073">68v, 69r</locus>
                  </decoNote>
                  <decoNote xml:id="d11">
                    Decorative designs:
                    <locus target="#1r #56r" facs="005 060">folss. 1r, 56r, </locus> (haräg);
                    <locus target="#1r #54" facs="005 058">1r, 54, </locus> (a line of alternating red and black dots);
                    <locus target="#54v #56r #66v" facs="059 060 071">54v, 56r, 66v</locus> (a line of full stops between lines of alternating red and black dots)
                  </decoNote>
                </decoDesc>
                <additions>
                  <list>
                    <item xml:id="a1">
                    <desc>
                      <locus target="#56v #57r" facs="061">Fols. 56v, 57r</locus>, Abba Qerǝlos, Patriarch of Alexandria and Abba Peṭros, Metropolitan of Ethiopia
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a2">
                    <desc type="OwnershipNote">
                      <locus target="#66v" facs="071"> f. 66v (margin</locus>): Note of ownership and prayer. The name of the original owner is erased
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a3">
                    <desc>
                      <locus target="#ivv(erso)" facs="004">Fol. ivv(erso)</locus>, pen trials
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e1">
                    <desc>
                      <locus target="#ir(ecto) #iir(ecto)" facs="001 002">Fols. ir(ecto), iir(ecto)</locus>, blank
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e2">
                    <desc>
                      Numbered quires: quires 2–7
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e3">
                    <desc>
                      Scribal intervention:
                      words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#3v #10v #14r #26v #62r" facs="008 015 018 031 066">folss. 3v, 10v, 14r, 26v, 62r, </locus>, etc.);
                      and lines of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#10v" facs="015">10v, </locus>);
                      and in the upper margin with a symbol (┴) marking the location where the text is to be inserted (<locus target="#55v" facs="060"> f, 55v, line 2</locus>);
                      text has been removed (e.g., <locus target="#61v" facs="066">61v</locus>)
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e4">
                    <desc>
                      <locus target="#4v" facs="009"> f. 4v, line 13</locus>; <locus target="#28r" facs="032"> f. 28r, line 13</locus>; <locus target="#53r" facs="057"> f. 53r, line 19</locus>, text is in the upper margin
                      with a symbol (┴) marking the location of the new section it introduces
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e5">
                    <desc>
                      <locus target="#6v" facs="011">Fol. 6v</locus>, line 19: text is in the upper margin with a symbol (+) marking the location of the new section it introduces
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                  </list>
                </additions>
                  <bindingDesc>
                    <binding xml:id="binding" contemporary="true">
                        <decoNote xml:id="b1">Parchment, 163 x 126 mm, four Coptic chain stitches attached with bridle attachments to rough-hewn boards of the traditional wood, covered in tooled leather, headband and tailband.</decoNote>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b2" type="bindingMaterial">
                           <material key="parchment"/>
                           <material key="wood"/>
                           <material key="leather"/>
                        </decoNote>
                    </binding>
                  </bindingDesc>
